<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Method - The National Angle"
  description="How The National Angle finds, verifies, labels, and updates its reporting and analysis."
>
  <article class="infoPage">
    <header class="infoHero">
      <div class="signalPills"><span>Method</span><span>Verification</span><span>Transparency</span></div>
      <h1>How we turn early evidence into useful reporting</h1>
      <p class="pageDeck">Original analysis depends on discipline. We use the following process to keep reporting useful without overstating what the evidence can prove.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="infoGrid methodGrid">
      <section><p class="cardLabel">01</p><h2>Start with observable evidence</h2><p>Stories should begin with material that readers can evaluate: public records, filings, legislation, research, official statements, datasets, direct observation, or credible original reporting.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">02</p><h2>Corroborate important claims</h2><p>We look for confirmation across independent sources and prefer primary sources where practical. Anonymous or unverified online claims are not sufficient evidence on their own.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">03</p><h2>Separate fact from interpretation</h2><p>Articles distinguish what happened from what it might mean. Plausible implications are framed as analysis, not certainty, and meaningful alternative explanations should be acknowledged.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">04</p><h2>Link the evidence</h2><p>When sources are publicly available and safe to share, articles should link to them so readers can inspect the underlying material.</p></section>
      <section><p class="cardLabel">05</p><h2>Correct material errors</h2><p>Substantive factual errors should be corrected promptly. Significant updates should be reflected in the article and its updated date rather than silently changing the record.</p></section>
    </div>

    <div class="infoActions"><a class="btn primary" href="/latest">Explore the reporting</a><a class="btn" href="/about">About the publication</a></div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
